==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unfellow
<hw>Un*fel"low</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>fellow</ets>.]</ety> <def>To prevent from being a
fellow or companion; to separate from one's fellows; to
dissever.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Death quite <qex>unfellows</qex> us.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unfellowed</ent>⟦br⟧
